The numeric value representing the quantity of specific OBJECT-TYPEs physically held on-hand, not including reserves, by a specific OBJECT-ITEM. For simulation purpose, it's mapped to the quantity of available and [operational + damaged] Equipment (without reserve) at the instant of the report in the unit. If simulation doesn't provide this attribute, it means that it doesn't manage damaged equipments. Its not used for consumables.

The precision is defined by assigning a value of 2 to define a number using kilometers as its units of measure; a value of 3 to define a number using 100 meters as its units of measure, a value of 4 to define a number using 10 meters as its units of measure, or a value of 5 to define a number using meters as its units of measure.
